\ Marking a long cons list must not recurse on the native C stack: a
\ length-N list once recursed N deep down the tail and overflowed under
\ gc. mark_value walks the tail spine iteratively, so a 1M-deep list
\ survives a collection instead of crashing. Reverting to recursive
\ tail-marking turns this into a SIGSEGV.
1 1000000 range array>cons gc 42 . cr

\ Non-tail nesting: each array holds the deeper one in element 0, not the
\ tail, so the tail loop cannot absorb it. Recursive marking on non-tail
\ children overflowed the C stack. mark descends a bounded number of C
\ frames, then defers deeper children to an explicit worklist, so arbitrary
\ nesting survives a collection instead of crashing.
[ 0 ] [: 0 2 array :] 200000 times gc 43 . cr
